President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued a proclamation declaring September 23 as National Hunting and Fishing Day. The proclamation recognizes the importance of hunting and fishing in American culture, as well as their role in conservation and the livelihoods of Tribal Nations. President Biden highlights his administration's efforts to conserve lands and waters, including establishing a goal to conserve or restore 30 percent of the nation's lands and waters by 2030. The administration has also protected iconic and sacred places and expanded access for hunting and fishing on public lands. The proclamation acknowledges the threat of climate change to wildlife and their habitats and emphasizes the administration's commitment to combatting the climate crisis. President Biden calls on Americans to observe National Hunting and Fishing Day and work together to protect the outdoors for future generations.